    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>36 Great Marlborough St</placeName>
                    <date>August 18<hi rend="superscript">th.</hi> 1838</date>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
<p>In pursuance of your directions in your letter of Feb<hi rend="superscript">y</hi>. 23<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. 1838, and in accordance with the plan of expenditure, which met (Octb<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. 11<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1837) the approval of the Lords Comm: of Her Majesty’s Treasury, I enclose the accounts for No<hi rend="superscript">o</hi> 1 of Part II and No<hi rend="superscript">o</hi> 1 of Part III, of the “Zoology of the Voyage of the Beagle”, which have both been published.—<ref target="#foot.f1"/> I beg leave to state, that as on the former occasion, I have superintended every expense, &amp; the terms agreed on with the artists. I presume, if the account meets with their Lordships approval, M<hi rend="superscript">rrs</hi>. Smith and Elder may as before, wait on M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sarjent<ref target="#foot.f2"/> at the Treasury Chambers for payment.</p>
<p>I have the honor to remain | Sir | Your obedient and obliged servant | Charles Darwin <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/> To | A. Y. Spearman Esq<hi rend="superscript">r</hi></p>
<p>Treasury Chambers.</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">3.3 Majesty’s] ‘y’ <hi rend="italic">over</hi> ‘e’</note>
                </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Preserved with this letter are two accounts from <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4407.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Smith, Elder &amp; Co</ref>., dated 18 May 1838 and 4 July 1838, detailing the various costs of <hi rend="italic">Mammalia,</hi> No. 1 and <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_650.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Birds</hi></ref>, No. 1. The total expenses were £39 6<hi rend="italic">s.</hi> 9<hi rend="italic">d.</hi> and £45 3<hi rend="italic">s.</hi> 2<hi rend="italic">d.</hi>, respectively.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_8072.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">William Sargent</ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
